<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="846" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111Sh4/6: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-27T13:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            27, 1920—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January
                                    27—9:51 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>25. I have wired to the military attaché at Saigon instructing him to
                                proceed to Yunnan to negotiate with local authorities concerning
                                release of Doctor Shelton.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>